DIGEST
SB 331 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Owen
Present law creates the Natural and Scenic Rivers System to protect, conserve, and replenish
state water bodies and designates certain rivers, streams, and bayous that are part of the
system.
Present law prohibits channelization, clearing and snagging, channel realignment and
reservoir construction on water bodies in the system.
Proposed law retains present law and creates certain exceptions and prohibitions for the
portion of the West Pearl River and tributaries lying between Lock 1 and the Rigolets, from
August 1, 2026, to August 1, 2031.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Adds R.S. 56:1855(Q))
Summary of Amendments Adopted by Senate
Committee Amendments Proposed by Senate Committee on Natural Resources to
the original bill
1. Reduce sunset period from 7 years to 5.
2. Add tributaries to defined area of river.
Senate Floor Amendments to engrossed bill
1. Remove reservoir construction from activities allowed or requiring a permit.
2. Prohibit new commercial or clustered residential development along a scenic
river as provided under present law.
